<body>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN10542" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="NEW">Select Address List</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10549" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Select the address list to use for <link href="text/swriter/01/mailmerge03.xhp">mail merge</link>, then click OK.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN1055A" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Add</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN1055E" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Click to open a file open dialog where you can select the address list file. If the selected file contains more than one table, you see the <link href="text/swriter/01/mm_seltab.xhp">Select Table</link> dialog next.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN10573" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Create<comment>screen mockup shows New</comment></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10589" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Opens the <link href="text/swriter/01/mm_newaddlis.xhp">New Address List</link> dialog, where you can enter and save a new address list.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN1059A" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Filter</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN1059E" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Click to open the <link href="text/shared/02/12090100.xhp">Standard Filter</link> dialog , where you can filter the recipients by logical conditions.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN105AF" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Edit</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN105B3" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Opens the <link href="text/swriter/01/mm_newaddlis.xhp">New Address List</link> dialog, where you can edit the selected address list.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN105C4" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Other table</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN105C8" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Opens the <link href="text/swriter/01/mm_seltab.xhp">Select Table</link> dialog, where you can select another table to use for mail merge.</paragraph>
</body>
